    {
      "id": "db60f81e79dceb54643546f278fb23c1956225af",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2011-08-10 06:11:55.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(8 inline comments)\n\nSeveral errors with this patch:\n- it appears that it would not work as-is, because of the critical missing OBD_CONNECT_MAX_EASIZE flag at connect time.  Without this, the MDS has no idea that the client understands large xattrs, and it needs to assume it does not.\n- the addition of the \"max_lov_ea_size\" flag is incorrect.\n- if this was being submitted for adding client-only support to 2.1, there are quite a number of patches for the server-side that would not be needed (all md[ds]/*, lvfs/*, osd-ldiskfs/*, ptlrpc/* changes should be dropped).\n\nThat said, I'm reluctant to add client-only support to 2.1 because it makes it difficult to test the client code, and it opens up the chance of compatibility issues if the code that is finally tested and landed for 2.2 is different for some reason.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "884fba828632d6258aa3e93653aeb04e59132c37",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2011-08-10 14:06:53.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nIt sounds like you want large stripe count will be a Lustre 2.3 feature with possible Lustre 2.2 client support.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
